This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dejanae A Baker in court.  Attorney Colin Patrick McGinn in court for Dejanae A Baker.  Attorney James C Griffin in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a status conference.  Defense requests a projected guilty plea hearing.  Court scheduled the matter as requested.  Case adjourned to Branch 2, Rm 635 CH.
Plea hearing scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Dejanae A Baker in court, appear in person with attorney Colin Patrick McGinn, appear in person.  Amanda Korin Kirklewski appeared in person for James C Griffin for the State of Wisconsin.  
Hearing held via Zoom. Defense requests a status conference date. Case adjourned, Branch 2 via Zoom.  Status conference scheduled for September 22, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Dejanae A Baker in court with attorney Colin Patrick McGinn, appear by video.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer J. Terrell. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 02.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 17, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 1 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders.

Defendant Dejanae A Baker in court with attorney Melissa Jane Fitzsimmons.  Defendant Dejanae A Baker in custody.  Lisa M Valenti-Jordan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Dejanae A Baker appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 02.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant she may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if she meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
